  <title translate="true">Defining Parameters</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading2_atoc_"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Defining Parameters</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">In the Layer Property Flow package, parameters can be used to define aquifer properties.  In this model, two parameters are used to define the hydraulic conductivity.  To see the definition of the parameters, select </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MODFLOW_Packages_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Model|MODFLOW Packages and Programs...</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> On the left, expand &quot;Flow&quot; and select the LPF package, and then click on HK to see the parameter definitions (fig. </text><conditional-text type="IF" value="CHM,HLP,HXS,HTML,DEMO,USER1,USER2,USER3"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">72</text><conditional-text type="ELSE"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">27</text><conditional-text type="END"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">). Parameter &quot;HK_Par1&quot; has a value of 150 and HK_Par2 has a value of 200.  Both parameters use Zone arrays.  HK_Par2 uses a multiplier array. Click </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Cancel</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> to close the dialog box.</text></para>
